Given the following program, identify all loop structures. Please write the identified lines (just copy the first line of code from this loop, e.g., for (xxx) {, while (xxx) {.) into a list: [a list of identified lines]. If no loop is identified, just give an empty list [].. The program is struct c {
  int d : 18;
};
int i_d;
int main() {
  struct c l;
  l.d = i_d;
  int n = i_d && l.d;
  i_d = l.d | -(l.d && l.d) - n;
}
.
